        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 1:06PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 106 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Custer, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Custer, Pringle, northwestern Wind Cave National Park, Blue Bell,
Center Lake, Stockade Lake, Custer State Park, Mount Coolidge, Legion
Lake, State Game Lodge, Crazy Horse Memorial, and Black Hills
Playhouse.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
